Interface DecimalVector<V extends DecimalVector<V>>

Type Parameters:
V - The vector itself (the result and parameter of various operations)
All Superinterfaces:

All Known Implementing Classes:
Decimal2, Decimal3, Decimal4, DecimalArrayVector, DecimalQuaternion
public interface DecimalVector<V extends DecimalVector<V>> extends BigVector<BigDecimal,V>
A mathematical vector which uses BigDecimal to represents its components. All fixed-size decimal vectors use the ABC notation as opposed to the XYZ notation of double vectors.
